  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes him:\\n\\n\"I telephoned an astrologer for an appointment and he sald: “Let me write it down first: Born October 3, 1924, right?\\n\\n“In Wallasey, Cheshire—yes, I need that for your latitude and longitude. And what time were you born?\"\\n\\nThis was my mother's problem. \\n\\nShe said, in a surprised voice over the long-distance — telephone: “Dear boy, I hardly remember, It was something nasty that happened in the night—I believe about 2 am.”\\n\\n(\"My 30s. Peep into the Future\" by Peter Chambers, ''The China Mail'', 10 June 1961, page 14).\\n",
